article.description: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 73, Long Island U. 55
article.headline: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 73, Long Island U. 55
article.linkText: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 73, Long Island U. 55
article.story: EDS: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 73, Long Island 55; RESTORES sport designator. EMMITSBURG, Md. (AP) -- Sam Atupem scored a game-high 17 points and Jeremy Goode and Chris Vann contributed 13 points each, and Mount St. Mary's defeated Long Island 73-55 Thursday night. The Mountaineers (3-4) took a 41-25 halftime lead after going on a 12-2 run late in the first half. Long Island (4-3) cut the deficit to 29-23 with 4:19 left in the period. The Mount responded by scoring the next 10 points. Long Island moved within 51-39 on a 3-pointer by senior Eugene Kotorobai with 13:14 to go, but the Blackbirds made just two field goals over the next nine minutes as Mount St. Mary's pulled away. The Mountaineers led by as much as 71-46 in the final minutes. Ron Manigault scored a team-high 15 points for Long Island.
